        "Name": "Titan",
        "Details": "Weighing in at a full hundred tons, the Titan was designed around a Vlar 300 standard fusion engine that limits its top speed to fifty-four kilometers per hour. While slow even by assault 'Mech standards, the use of a standard engine provides exceptional survivability, as the 'Mech can continue operating even after catastrophic torso damage. Nineteen tons of standard armor give the Titan formidable protection across its frame. This Titan variant was introduced at the same time as the TI-1Aj. It uses the same SRM-4 and double heat sink count, but drops the jump jets to carry a third PPC, all three standard models to reduce the 'Mech's heat load.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
